<dl id="n11013a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n11" href="#n11013a">N11 (VI.B.5)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n11all.htm#n11013a"> 13(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Blind me <font color="red"><sup><teeny>|a</teeny></sup></font><span class="strike"><span class="striketext">in</span></span> with<span class="strike"><span class="striketext">in</span></span><font color="red"><sup><teeny>a|</teeny></sup></font> your <font color="red"><sup><teeny>|a</teeny></sup></font><span class="strike"><span class="striketext">deep</span></span> dark<font color="red"><sup><teeny>a|</teeny></sup></font> <font color="red"><sup><teeny>|a</teeny></sup></font><span class="strike"><span class="striketext">embraces</span></span> nearness<font color="red"><sup><teeny>a|</teeny></sup></font> / beloved <font color="red"><sup><teeny>|a</teeny></sup></font><span class="strike"><span class="striketext">foe</span></span> enemy<font color="red"><sup><teeny>a|</teeny></sup></font> of my will, / <span class="strike"><span class="striketext">I dare <font color="green">[blank]</font></span></span> / I dare not now <font color="red"><sup><teeny>|a</teeny></sup></font><span class="strike"><span class="striketext">withold <font color="green">[blank]</font></span></span> <font color="red"><sup><teeny>|b</teeny></sup></font><span class="strike"><span class="striketext">deny and suffer the call I dread</span></span> withstand the / cold touch I dread<font color="red"><sup><teeny>b|</teeny></sup></font><font color="red"><sup><teeny>a|</teeny></sup></font> / Draw from me still / My <span class="strike"><span class="striketext">life,</span></span> slow life. Bend <span class="strike"><span class="striketext">down on</span></span> deeper / on me, threatening head, / <font color="red"><sup><teeny>|a</teeny></sup></font><span class="strike"><span class="striketext">Prouder by my abasement</span></span> Proud of my <font color="red"><sup><teeny>|b</teeny></sup></font><span class="strike"><span class="striketext">downfall</span></span> abasement<font color="red"><sup><teeny>b|</teeny></sup></font> yet<font color="red"><sup><teeny>a|</teeny></sup></font> / Pitying, <font color="red"><sup><teeny>|a</teeny></sup></font>remembering<font color="red"><sup><teeny>a|</teeny></sup></font> / Him who is, him who was. </blockquote> <dd class="well"><mm class="note">Note: Written sideways on page. Draft of second stanza of Joyce&apos;s poem, &lsquo;A Prayer&rsquo; (published in 1927 in <i>Pomes Penyeach</i>: <br>Blind me with your dark nearness, O have mercy, beloved enemy of my will! <br>I dare not withstand the cold touch that I dread. <br>Draw from me still <br>My slow life! Bend deeper on me, threatening head, <br>Proud by my downfall, remembering, <br>pitying Him who is, him who was! ). <br>See notecooks pages 11 and 15 for the first and third stanzas. The TS of the poem is dated 18 May 1924.</mm> </dd></dl>
